{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Usually I like working in my shop,"},{"time":2625,"text":"but when it's raining and the driveway outside turns into a river,"},{"time":6958,"text":"then I just love it."},{"time":8998,"text":"And I'll cut some wood and drill some holes and watch the water,"},{"time":12329,"text":"and maybe I'll have to walk around and look for washers."},{"time":15208,"text":"You have no idea how much time I spend."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18140,"text":"This is the \"Double Raindrop.\""},{"time":20167,"text":"Of all my sculptures, it's the most talkative."},{"time":28430,"text":"It adds together the interference pattern"},{"time":31442,"text":"from two raindrops that land near each other."},{"time":34721,"text":"Instead of expanding circles, they're expanding hexagons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44945,"text":"All the sculptures move by mechanical means."},{"time":54890,"text":"Do you see how there's three peaks to the yellow sine wave?"},{"time":59125,"text":"Right here I'm adding a sine wave with four peaks and turning it on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80644,"text":"Eight hundred two-liter soda bottles --"},{"time":84110,"text":"oh yea."},{"time":85854,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":98259,"text":"Four hundred aluminum cans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104517,"text":"Tule is a reed that's native to California,"},{"time":107277,"text":"and the best thing about working with it is that it smells just delicious."},{"time":125835,"text":"A single drop of rain"},{"time":128783,"text":"increasing amplitude."},{"time":152883,"text":"The spiral eddy that trails a paddle on a rafting trip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168263,"text":"This adds together four different waves."},{"time":171138,"text":"And here I'm going to pull out the double wavelengths"},{"time":174059,"text":"and increase the single."},{"time":177407,"text":"The mechanism that drives it has nine motors"},{"time":180348,"text":"and about 3,000 pulleys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192516,"text":"Four hundred and forty-five strings in a three-dimensional weave."},{"time":197173,"text":"Transferred to a larger scale --"},{"time":200012,"text":"actually a lot larger, with a lot of help --"},{"time":203090,"text":"14,064 bicycle reflectors --"},{"time":206857,"text":"a 20-day install."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229683,"text":"\"Connected\" is a collaboration"},{"time":231375,"text":"with choreographer Gideon Obarzanek."},{"time":235179,"text":"Strings attached to dancers."},{"time":238520,"text":"This is very early rehearsal footage,"},{"time":240942,"text":"but the finished work's on tour"},{"time":243304,"text":"and is actually coming through L.A. in a couple weeks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252139,"text":"A pair of helices and 40 wooden slats."},{"time":277771,"text":"Take your finger and draw this line."},{"time":281000,"text":"Summer, fall, winter, spring,"},{"time":285000,"text":"noon, dusk, dark, dawn."},{"time":291237,"text":"Have you ever seen those stratus clouds"},{"time":294500,"text":"that go in parallel stripes across the sky?"},{"time":297173,"text":"Did you know that's a continuous sheet of cloud"},{"time":299768,"text":"that's dipping in and out of the condensation layer?"},{"time":303365,"text":"What if every seemingly isolated object"},{"time":306198,"text":"was actually just where the continuous wave of that object"},{"time":310042,"text":"poked through into our world?"},{"time":313523,"text":"The Earth is neither flat nor round."},{"time":317900,"text":"It's wavy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322323,"text":"It sounds good, but I'll bet you know in your gut that it's not the whole truth,"},{"time":327821,"text":"and I'll tell you why."},{"time":329379,"text":"I have a two-year-old daughter who's the best thing ever."},{"time":331375,"text":"And I'm just going to come out and say it:"},{"time":333458,"text":"My daughter is not a wave."},{"time":336993,"text":"And you might say, \"Surely, Rueben, if you took even just the slightest step back,"},{"time":341573,"text":"the cycles of hunger and eating,"},{"time":344333,"text":"waking and sleeping, laughing and crying"},{"time":347173,"text":"would emerge as pattern.\""},{"time":349784,"text":"But I would say, \"If I did that,"},{"time":352411,"text":"too much would be lost.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":355900,"text":"This tension between the need to look deeper"},{"time":360629,"text":"and the beauty and immediacy of the world,"},{"time":363583,"text":"where if you even try to look deeper you've already missed what you're looking for,"},{"time":367285,"text":"this tension is what makes the sculptures move."},{"time":370356,"text":"And for me, the path between these two extremes"},{"time":372867,"text":"takes the shape of a wave."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375602,"text":"Let me show you one more."},{"time":420100,"text":"Thank you very much. Thanks."},{"time":423529,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":425710,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426942,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":431406,"text":"June Cohen: Looking at each of your sculptures,"},{"time":433179,"text":"they evoke so many different images."},{"time":435607,"text":"Some of them are like the wind and some are like waves,"},{"time":438142,"text":"and sometimes they look alive and sometimes they seem like math."},{"time":441027,"text":"Is there an actual inspiration behind each one?"},{"time":443531,"text":"Are you thinking of something physical or somthing tangible as you design it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":447087,"text":"RM: Well some of them definitely have a direct observation --"},{"time":450227,"text":"like literally two raindrops falling,"},{"time":453042,"text":"and just watching that pattern is so stunning."},{"time":455917,"text":"And then just trying to figure out how to make that using stuff."},{"time":461621,"text":"I like working with my hands."},{"time":464165,"text":"There's nothing better than cutting a piece of wood"},{"time":466375,"text":"and trying to make it move."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468125,"text":"JC: And does it ever change?"},{"time":469875,"text":"Do you think you're designing one thing,"},{"time":471000,"text":"and then when it's produced it looks like something else?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":472750,"text":"RM: The \"Double Raindrop\" I worked on for nine months,"},{"time":476208,"text":"and when I finally turned it on,"},{"time":478565,"text":"I actually hated it."},{"time":482208,"text":"The very moment I turned it on, I hated it."},{"time":486333,"text":"It was like a really deep-down gut reaction, and I wanted to throw it out."},{"time":489681,"text":"And I happened to have a friend who was over,"},{"time":491825,"text":"and he said, \"Why don't you just wait.\""},{"time":493837,"text":"And I waited, and the next day I liked it a bit better,"},{"time":498206,"text":"the next day I liked it a bit better, and now I really love it."},{"time":501167,"text":"And so I guess, one, the gut reactions a little bit wrong sometimes,"},{"time":505833,"text":"and two, it does not look like as expected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508375,"text":"JC: The relationship evolves over time."},{"time":510792,"text":"Well thank you so much. That was a gorgeous treat for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511667,"text":"RM: Thanks. (JC: Thank you, Reuben.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":514554,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}